==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: amyloidosis
<hw>am`y*loi*do"sis</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧m`⟦icr⟧*loi*d⟦omac⟧"s⟦icr⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A disorder characterized by deposit
of extracellular amyloid{2} in organs or tissues in an amount that
interferes with normal function of the affected organ; it is often
secondary to chronic rheumatoid arthritis or tuberculosis or multiple
myeloma. Called also <altname>amyloid degeneration</altname>
<altname>waxy degeneration</altname> and <altname>lardaceous
degeneration</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> + <source>AS</source>]</p>

<p><ent>amylolysis</ent>⟦br⟧
